observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Health Office, the Human Resource Management Office, and other concerned offices to submit the following documents:
The list of public health workers, including Barangay Health Workers, determined and approved by the Local Health Board;
Specific authority from the head of the agency the claimants to physically report and respond to the public health emergency during the state of national emergency indicating therein the assigned work stations/health facilities for COVID-19, the prescribed official working hours, and their duties and responsibilities;
List of eligible health workers indicating their positions, compensation/s entitled to, and days physically present;
Certification attesting to the truthfulness of the contents of the report and adequate consent for sharing of data obtained from the personnel involved. The certification must be signed by the head of the human resource or personnel division and the head of the health facility, clearly indicating his/her designation or position;
Daily Time Records showing the actual date and time of the services rendered by the claimants as certified by the head of the hospital, laboratory, or medical and quarantine facility, or his/her authorized representative; and
Accomplishment Reports showing that the claimants have provided direct treatment and support care to COVID-19 patients.

We recommended that Management:
submit justification on the non-submission of awarded contracts and POs to the office of the auditor, in compliance with Section 3 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009;
direct the personnel in-charge to furnish the Office of the Auditor with copies of the Contracts and POs together with its supporting documents within the prescribed period as required under COA Circular No. 2009-001;
impose disciplinary action against defaulting personnel for any unjustified failure to comply with the requirements as provided in Section 4.1, COA Circular No. 2009-001

